'''Ubrikkian Steamworks''' was a subsidiary of [[Ubrikkian Industries/Legends|Ubrikkian Industries]].

Ubrikkian Steamworks manufactured droids, most notably the [[DD-13 medical assistant droid/Legends|DD-13 cybernetic surgical droid]] and an earlier [[Ubrikkian Steamworks medical unit|medical unit]] responsible for making [[Grievous/Legends|Grievous]] into a cyborg. [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] disliked the "Galactic Chopper" droid so much that he personally prevented the renewal of Ubrikkian's DD-13 supply contract.

Despite a planned redesign of the DD-13 line, Ubrikkian retired the [[Medical droid/Legends|medical droids]] and focused on the [[DD-19 "Overseer" labor pool droid|DD-19 labor pool droid]].

{{Company-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
''[[The New Essential Guide to Droids]]'' author [[Daniel Wallace]] named Ubrikkian Steamworks for his interest in the [[Wikipedia:science-fiction|science-fiction]] sub-genre known as [[Wikipedia:Steampunk|steampunk]].<ref name="Blog-danwallace|52">{{Blog|danwallace|52|Endnotes for The New Essential Guide to Droids: PART 1 OF 3}}</ref>

